1
00:00:57,181 --> 00:00:58,881
Bring young Gawain here.

2
00:01:07,019 --> 00:01:08,290
The king would speak with you.

3
00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:47,779
Where is thy mother?

4
00:01:49,641 --> 00:01:51,643
She was not feeling herself, my lord.

5
00:01:53,453 --> 00:01:56,450
Then come. Sit here, besides us.

6
00:01:57,616 --> 00:01:59,060
Besides me and my queen.

7
00:02:01,877 --> 00:02:02,890
That is not my place.

8
00:02:04,758 --> 00:02:07,777
No. Let it be, today.

9
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:10,283
Its owner is away.

10
00:02:11,896 --> 00:02:13,345
Who knows when he will return?

11
00:02:16,093 --> 00:02:16,533
Please.

12
00:02:26,272 --> 00:02:27,536
Good to see you, Gawain.

13
00:02:29,560 --> 00:02:33,570
Good to have one's family by one's side.

14
00:02:36,129 --> 00:02:36,780
One's blood.

15
00:02:38,677 --> 00:02:42,181
Surely your knights have spilled enough blood in your name

16
00:02:42,206 --> 00:02:43,829
to bind them closer to you than I.

17
00:02:44,757 --> 00:02:45,077
True.

18
00:02:48,145 --> 00:02:49,555
But you are my sister's boy,

19
00:02:51,675 --> 00:02:53,062
queefed from her womb.
20
00:02:55,209 --> 00:02:55,922
They are not.

21
00:02:57,524 --> 00:03:00,671
I look out upon my friends here today

22
00:03:00,696 --> 00:03:11,271
and I see... songs... no muse could ever sing or dream of.

23
00:03:15,355 --> 00:03:17,919
But I turn to thee and I see what?

24
00:03:19,009 --> 00:03:22,509
I recognize but I do not know thee.

25
00:03:23,442 --> 00:03:27,588
I say this not in reproach, but regret that

26
00:03:28,022 --> 00:03:31,271
I have never asked you to sit at my side before this day

27
00:03:32,422 --> 00:03:36,389
or upon my knee when thy was newborn.

28
00:03:40,111 --> 00:03:41,248
But now it is Christmas,

29
00:03:43,699 --> 00:03:45,082
and I wish to build bridges.

30
00:03:48,428 --> 00:03:50,742
So before we make merry...

31
00:03:54,642 --> 00:03:55,990
you make for me a gift.

32
00:03:58,156 --> 00:03:59,738
You tell me a tale of yourself,

33
00:04:01,355 --> 00:04:02,559
so that I might know thee.

34
00:04:18,871 --> 00:04:20,805
I have none to tell, King.

35
00:04:23,692 --> 00:04:24,426
Yet.

36
00:04:27,188 --> 00:04:28,865
You have none to tell yet.

37
00:04:31,444 --> 00:04:31,861
Yet.

38
00:04:33,744 --> 00:04:35,392
Look around you, young Gawain.

39
00:04:37,373 --> 00:04:38,257
What do you see?

40
00:04:45,955 --> 00:04:46,888
I see legends.

41
00:04:49,855 --> 00:04:52,419
Do not take your place amongst them idly.

42
00:04:55,296 --> 00:04:55,859
Hmm.

43
00:05:03,746 --> 00:05:07,196
So who else then... hmm?

44
00:05:13,936 --> 00:05:14,678
Friends...

45
00:05:20,444 --> 00:05:26,344
Brothers... (Brothers...) Brothers and... sisters all. (…sisters all)

46
00:05:28,190 --> 00:05:33,973
I thank thee for breaking bread with me this blessed day.

47
00:05:35,553 --> 00:05:36,667
And it is blessed...

48
00:05:39,118 --> 00:05:44,769
for out my window this morn I looked,

49
00:05:45,617 --> 00:05:53,794
and I saw a land shaped...by your hands.

50
00:05:56,962 --> 00:06:00,798
You have lain those same hands upon our Saxon brethren,

51
00:06:00,899 --> 00:06:07,190
who now in your shadow bow their heads like babes.

52
00:06:08,592 --> 00:06:11,534
Peace, peace you have brought to your kingdom,

53
00:06:12,076 --> 00:06:17,882
so it is in peace that I... I now say to you...

54
00:06:19,708 --> 00:06:25,619
that I... I am the luckiest here today...

55
00:06:28,794 --> 00:06:30,428
because I am amongst thee.

56
00:06:34,534 --> 00:06:35,801
I am amongst thee.

57
00:06:39,180 --> 00:06:45,088
So before we celebrate the birth of our Christ,

58
00:06:46,251 --> 00:06:50,998
let us honor one of our own who has done great things in His name.

59
00:06:53,128 --> 00:06:57,488
So a tale, or... Or a show perhaps.

60
00:06:58,421 --> 00:06:59,205
What have thee?

61
00:07:02,132 --> 00:07:05,030
Who can regale me and my queen

62
00:07:05,055 --> 00:07:12,797
with some myth or canto of thine own purport?

